    • posToAngles

      public edu.wpi.first.math.Pair<Double,Double> posToAngles(edu.wpi.first.math.geometry.Translation2d goal, boolean useTopPossibility)
      This converts a goal to two angles for an arm. Essentially meaning we can say, "arm, go there." instead of saying, "Arm set angle to this and this." (Warning: Contains side effect of setting default to the one used here)
      Parameters:
      goal - The position at the end of the arm
      useTopPossibility - Whether or not the segment 1 is angled upwards or downwards
      Returns:
      A pair of angles in radians of both segments
